<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-03-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-03-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="1742" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1742">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.0145/5.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">American
                                    Ambassador</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 148.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-03-11">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 11, 1911</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department has received your No. 466
                            of the 13th ultimo reporting further concerning the Russian law
                            extending to twelve miles from low-water mark the area of supervision by
                            the Russian customs authorities.</p>
                        <p>The Department awaits the reply promised to you by the Russian Minister
                            for Foreign Affairs and your comments thereon.</p>
                        <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Alvey A. Adee.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>